description:
Defines the Riverpod state management architecture for LexMastery.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Riverpod State Management

Riverpod is the only approved state management solution.

Never introduce:

- Bloc
- Cubit
- Provider
- Redux
- MobX
- GetX

---

# Philosophy

State should be:

- Immutable
- Predictable
- Feature-scoped
- Testable
- Explicit

State exists to describe the UI.

Business logic never belongs inside Widgets.

---

# Feature Ownership

Each feature owns its providers.

Example:

features/
    authentication/
        application/
        presentation/
            providers/

Avoid global providers unless truly global.

---

# Provider Types

Preferred:

AsyncNotifierProvider

NotifierProvider

FutureProvider

StreamProvider

StateProvider is allowed only for ephemeral UI state.

Examples:

- selected tab
- expanded tile
- current page

Never store business state in StateProvider.

---

# Controller Responsibilities

Controllers coordinate:

- repositories
- use cases
- state updates
- analytics
- navigation events

Controllers must never:

- parse JSON
- perform HTTP requests directly
- render widgets

---

# State Objects

Every controller exposes a single immutable state.

Example:

LoginState

DashboardState

QuizState

Always use Freezed.

---

# Async State

Represent every async operation explicitly.

Use:

Initial

Loading

Refreshing

Success

Empty

Error

Avoid boolean flags like:

isLoading

hasError

---

# Watching Providers

Use:

ref.watch()

only when rebuilds are required.

Use:

ref.read()

for commands.

Use:

ref.listen()

for:

- snackbars
- dialogs
- navigation
- side effects

---

# Derived State

Never duplicate state.

Compute derived values using providers.

---

# Pagination

Pagination belongs inside controllers.

Expose:

- items
- page
- hasMore
- loadingMore

---

# Search

Debounce requests.

Cancel obsolete searches.

Never issue duplicate requests.

---

# Error Handling

Convert infrastructure exceptions into domain failures.

Never expose raw Dio exceptions to the UI.

---

# Optimistic Updates

Use only when appropriate.

Rollback on failure.

---

# Testing

Every provider must have unit tests.

Business logic should be testable without Flutter.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Generate:

- controller
- immutable state
- provider
- tests

Keep widgets free of business logic.